      "description": "Dexterity Saving Throw: DC [[lookup @save.dc.value activity=YorssyWMumAsvzx3]], [[lookup @target.affects.special activity=YorssyWMumAsvzx3]] by the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} (the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} can have only one creature swallowed at a time).\n\nFailure: The [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} swallows the target, which is no longer &amp;Reference[Grappled apply=false]. While swallowed, a creature has the &amp;Reference[Blinded apply=false] and &amp;Reference[Restrained apply=false] conditions, has Total Cover against attacks and other effects outside the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster}, and takes [[/damage average activity=zrWNjO9mkbN28spL]] damage at the start of each of the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster}'s turns.\n\nIf the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} takes 30 damage or more on a single turn from the swallowed creature, the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} must succeed on a [[/save format=long activity=rGeGukkm2t2fXsoy]] at the end of that turn or regurgitate the creature, which falls in a space within [[lookup @range.value activity=rGeGukkm2t2fXsoy]] [[lookup @range.units activity=rGeGukkm2t2fXsoy]]. of the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} and has the &amp;Reference[Prone apply=false] condition. If the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} dies, a swallowed creature is no longer Restrained and can escape from the corpse by using 15 feet of movement, exiting Prone.",
